Source: rake-rubyee1.8
Section: ruby
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Leonid Borisenko <leo.borisenko@gmail.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 7), cdbs, rubyee1.8, ruby-pkg-tools, graphviz
Standards-Version: 3.8.4
Homepage: http://rake.rubyforge.com
Vcs-Git: git://github.com/130/rake-rubyee18-debian-package.git
Vcs-Browser: http://github.com/130/rake-rubyee18-debian-package

Package: rake-rubyee1.8
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, librake-rubyee1.8
Recommends: rake-doc
Description: A ruby build program (Ruby Enterprise Edition 1.8)
 Rake is a simple ruby build program with capabilities similar to make.
 .
 Rake has the following features:
 * Rakefiles (rakes version of Makefiles) are completely defined in
   standard Ruby syntax. No XML files to edit. No quirky Makefile
   syntax to worry about (is that a tab or a space?)
 * Users can specify tasks with prerequisites.
 * Rake supports rule patterns to sythesize implicit tasks.
 * Rake is lightweight. It can be distributed with other
   projects as a single file. Projects that depend upon
   rake do not require that rake be installed on target
   systems.
 .
 This package provides executable of Rake for Ruby Enterprise Edition 1.8.

